progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"cmux claude-hook session-start\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"0e908f0d-1c9b-4f15-925c-b8df0f74c999\",\"toolUseID\":\"0e908f0d-1c9b-4f15-925c-b8df0f74c999\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T20:12:33.023Z\",\"uuid\":\"bad9d6da-8e9a-4457-a80c-31c17091f679\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"bad9d6da-8e9a-4457-a80c-31c17091f679\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"7d500980-585e-442f-839d-e2308b5d8e1f\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"joyful-chasing-mochi\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks-handlers/session-start.sh\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"0e908f0d-1c9b-4f15-925c-b8df0f74c999\",\"toolUseID\":\"0e908f0d-1c9b-4f15-925c-b8df0f74c999\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T20:12:33.023Z\",\"uuid\":\"1cf3c9b6-e607-4419-8335-94268377d9ee\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"1cf3c9b6-e607-4419-8335-94268377d9ee\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"7d500980-585e-442f-839d-e2308b5d8e1f\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"joyful-chasing-mochi\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Review: Kiro-Specific Changes in Agent-Agnostic Files\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe `alisha/kiro-oneshot` branch adds Kiro agent support. The Kiro-specific logic is properly isolated in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/`, but several agent-agnostic files were also modified. This review assesses whether those shared-file changes are necessary and whether any can be moved into the Kiro package.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## File-by-File Analysis\\n\\n### 1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` — stdin timeout + `ErrEmptyHookInput`\\n\\n**Changes:** Replaced synchronous `io.ReadAll(stdin)` with a goroutine + 500ms `select` timeout. Added exported `ErrEmptyHookInput` sentinel error.\\n\\n**Why it's here:** Kiro IDE keeps stdin pipes open without sending EOF, causing `io.ReadAll` to block forever. The timeout prevents hanging.\\n\\n**Verdict: KEEP in shared code, but with concerns.**\\n\\n- The sentinel error (`ErrEmptyHookInput`) is cleanly designed — Kiro's `readHookInputOrEmpty()` checks for it with `errors.Is()`, which is the right pattern.\\n- However, the **goroutine + timeout approach has a goroutine leak**: when the timeout fires, the goroutine calling `io.ReadAll` is abandoned but never terminates (it blocks forever on the open stdin pipe). This is a resource leak that persists for the lifetime of the process.\\n\\n**Recommendation:**\\n- **Cannot move to Kiro package** — `ReadAndParseHookInput` is the shared helper all agents call; the fix must live here.\\n- **Fix the goroutine leak**: The leaking goroutine is low-severity (hook processes are short-lived), but it's still worth documenting with a comment, or better, accepting `context.Context` so callers can bound the goroutine's lifetime. At minimum, add a comment acknowledging the leak.\\n- Consider whether the old behavior (returning error on empty stdin) should remain the default, with Kiro wrapping it. Currently `ErrEmptyHookInput` is returned to ALL agents on empty stdin — previously it was an anonymous `errors.New(\\\"empty hook input\\\")` that agents couldn't match with `errors.Is`. This is a **behavioral change**: agents that previously got an opaque error now get a matchable sentinel. This is fine but worth noting.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — `agentUsesTerminal()`\\n\\n**Changes:** Added `agentUsesTerminal()` predicate that returns true only for `AgentTypeKiro`. Modified the PrepareCommitMsg fast path from `if !hasTTY()` to `if !hasTTY() || agentUsesTerminal(state.AgentType)`.\\n\\n**Why it's here:** Kiro runs in tmux, so `hasTTY()` returns true even when the *agent* is committing (not the user). Without this, the hook would prompt the user during an agent-driven commit.\\n\\n**Verdict: MUST stay in shared code (strategy layer), but the hardcoded agent check is concerning.**\\n\\nThe strategy layer necessarily handles all agents — `PrepareCommitMsg` runs as a git hook and must decide per-agent. However:\\n\\n- **`agentUsesTerminal()` hardcodes `agent.AgentTypeKiro`** — this is a Kiro-specific check leaking into strategy code.\\n- **Better pattern: Use an optional interface.** The codebase already has 8 optional interfaces (`TranscriptPreparer`, `HookResponseWriter`, etc.). A `TerminalAgent` interface (or a method on `HookSupport` like `UsesTerminal() bool`) would let the agent declare this trait, and the strategy would do a type assertion instead of checking agent names.\\n\\n**Recommendation:**\\n- Add a small optional interface (e.g., `TerminalAgent`) to `agent/agent.go`, have Kiro implement it, and replace the hardcoded check in `manual_commit_hooks.go` with a type assertion. This removes the Kiro import from the strategy package entirely.\\n- Alternatively, if adding an interface feels heavy for a single boolean, add a `UsesTerminal` field to the session state (set by the agent at session start). The strategy already reads session state — no new interface needed.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — Empty TranscriptPath handling\\n\\n**Changes:** When `state.TranscriptPath == \\\"\\\"` and no shadow branch exists, instead of erroring, creates an empty `ExtractedSessionData{}`.\\n\\n**Why it's here:** Kiro's transcript isn't available during mid-turn commits (SQLite not populated yet). Without this, condensation fails when a commit happens before the transcript exists.\\n\\n**Verdict: KEEP — genuinely generic.**\\n\\n- The logic is agent-agnostic: \\\"if no transcript is available, create a minimal checkpoint anyway\\\". Any future agent with deferred transcript persistence benefits.\\n- The code doesn't reference Kiro at all (just a comment saying \\\"e.g., Kiro's deferred SQLite persistence\\\").\\n- The alternative path still errors on `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript` failure, so this only changes behavior for the specific case of empty TranscriptPath.\\n\\n**No changes recommended.** This is well-placed shared logic.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_git.go` — TranscriptPath backfill in SaveStep\\n\\n**Changes:** Added 4 lines: if `state.TranscriptPath == \\\"\\\"` and `step.TranscriptPath != \\\"\\\"`, backfill it.\\n\\n**Verdict: KEEP — genuinely generic.**\\n\\n- Same pattern as condensation: handles deferred transcript availability.\\n- The guard (`if state.TranscriptPath == \\\"\\\"`) makes it a no-op for all existing agents (they set TranscriptPath at session start).\\n- Clean, minimal, and doesn't reference Kiro.\\n\\n**No changes recommended.**\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` — Two changes\\n\\n#### 5a. Empty repository: `NewSilentError(...)` → `return nil`\\n\\n**Verdict: KEEP — generic bugfix.**\\n\\nThis is not Kiro-specific. Returning `SilentError` caused unnecessary error logging for a benign condition (new repo with no commits). Returning `nil` is the right behavior for all agents.\\n\\n#### 5b. TranscriptPath backfill in `transitionSessionTurnEnd`\\n\\n**Changes:** Added 4 lines to backfill `turnState.TranscriptPath` from `event.SessionRef` if empty.\\n\\n**Verdict: KEEP — genuinely generic.**\\n\\nSame pattern as the SaveStep backfill. Ensures the transcript path is available in session state before the state machine transition. Agent-agnostic, no-op for existing agents.\\n\\n**No changes recommended.**\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go` — Clear TranscriptPath on rewind\\n\\n**Changes:** After resetting the shadow branch to a checkpoint, clears `state.TranscriptPath` so subsequent condensation reads from the shadow branch (not the stale live transcript file).\\n\\n**Verdict: KEEP — genuinely generic.**\\n\\n- This is a rewind correctness fix. After rewinding, the live transcript file may contain data beyond the rewind point. Reading from it would create incorrect checkpoints.\\n- Applies to any agent with a persistent transcript file.\\n- Graceful error handling (warns, doesn't fail).\\n\\n**No changes recommended.**\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 7. `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go` — Kiro import\\n\\n**Changes:** Added `_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro\\\"` import.\\n\\n**Verdict: KEEP — required.**\\n\\nThis is the standard agent registration pattern. Every agent has a blank import here for `init()` self-registration. This is expected and correct.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 8. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — Minor cleanup of `sessionsWithContent` nil check\\n\\n**Changes:** Removed the `if len(sessionsWithContent) > 0` guard around agent type extraction, since the code already returns early if `sessionsWithContent` is empty (line ~400).\\n\\n**Verdict: KEEP — correct cleanup.**\\n\\nThe guard was dead code — `sessionsWithContent` is guaranteed non-empty at that point. Removing it improves readability.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\n| File | Change | Kiro-specific? | Can move to Kiro? | Recommendation |\\n|------|--------|:-:|:-:|----------------|\\n| `agent/event.go` | stdin timeout + sentinel error | Motivated by Kiro, generic fix | **No** | Keep; document goroutine leak |\\n| `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | `agentUsesTerminal()` | **Yes** (hardcodes Kiro) | **Partially** | Replace hardcode with optional interface or session state flag |\\n| `strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` | Empty TranscriptPath fallback | No | No | Keep as-is |\\n| `strategy/manual_commit_git.go` | TranscriptPath backfill | No | No | Keep as-is |\\n| `lifecycle.go` | Empty repo fix + TranscriptPath backfill | No | No | Keep as-is |\\n| `strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go` | Clear TranscriptPath on rewind | No | No | Keep as-is |\\n| `hooks_cmd.go` | Agent registration import | Standard pattern | No | Keep as-is |\\n\\n## Recommended Changes\\n\\n### 1. Remove Kiro hardcode from `agentUsesTerminal()` (medium priority)\\n\\n**Option A — Optional interface (preferred, follows existing patterns):**\\n\\n```go\\n// In agent/agent.go:\\n// TerminalAgent is implemented by agents that run inside a terminal emulator\\n// (e.g., Kiro in tmux). These agents have hasTTY()=true even when the agent\\n// is committing, requiring special handling in git hooks.\\ntype TerminalAgent interface {\\n    Agent\\n    UsesTerminal() bool\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThen in `manual_commit_hooks.go`, replace:\\n```go\\nfunc agentUsesTerminal(agentType types.AgentType) bool {\\n    return agentType == agent.AgentTypeKiro\\n}\\n```\\nwith a lookup that checks the agent registry for the `TerminalAgent` interface.\\n\\n**Option B — Session state flag (simpler):**\\nAdd `UsesTerminal bool` to `SessionState`. Set it at session start from agent metadata. Strategy reads it from state without knowing agent types.\\n\\n### 2. Document goroutine leak in `ReadAndParseHookInput` (low priority)\\n\\nAdd a comment noting that on timeout, the `io.ReadAll` goroutine is abandoned. Since hook processes are short-lived, this is acceptable but should be documented.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n- Run `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` after any changes\\n- The `agentUsesTerminal` refactor should be covered by existing `manual_commit_hooks_test.go` tests\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-kiro-oneshot/3e28b093-94b1-45ab-9761-47571d24013d.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"c16df4cf-03ac-4395-ac82-ef140733e047\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T20:12:32.507Z\",\"p